            <p>1.1 Client is encouraged to seek independent advice. Client specifically warrants that Client has been recommended to, and has had the opportunity to seek and obtain independent health care advice from an appropriately qualified health care practitioner in relation to any health care services that client may select through Company Choice Matching Services. Client warrants that Client is making the decision to engage the Medical Provider, and possibly travel, solely based upon Client's own independent investigation and analysis, and any discussions Client may have had with the medical provider and with Client's own health care and legal advisors in Client's home country. In the event that Client's selection requires travel, Client is solely responsible for discussing with Client's physician(s) Client's initial health care fitness for travel, the health risks associated with such travel (including possible unscheduled delays and changes of itinerary), the health care services obtained, post-treatment follow-up care and any recommended activity and travel restrictions, medications, and similar matters, and establishing a travel itinerary consistent with Client's health care fitness. Client acknowledges and agrees that Client is not relying on any representations or warranties, express or implied, from Company or its managers, members, agents, representatives, successors and assignees (the “Company Parties”) in selecting the medical provider and/or agreeing to engage their services.</p>
            <p>1.2 Client shall make informed choices regarding services. Client agrees that Client is relying solely upon the advice of Client's own physicians, domestically and abroad, and any other health care or legal advisors selected by Client, and not upon the advice or representations of the Company. Parties in deciding, as applicable, to (a) forego treatment in Client's home country; (b) travel; (c) undergo the scheduled health care procedures; and (d) undertake post-treatment travel and/or other activities, including without limitation, return to Client's home country. Client is relying upon the Provider of health care services, and not upon any Company Party, to satisfactorily explain Client's diagnosis, the recommended procedure(s), other relevant treatment options, including all associated risks and the likely outcome of the recommended procedure(s), as well as the prognosis and the risk of foregoing the recommended procedure(s) and any health risks associated with any travel and any travel following treatment.</p>

          <p>1.3 Client shall provide complete and accurate information to Company and all medical providers. Client agrees that all health care information provided by Client to Company and/or the medical providers hall be true, accurate and complete to the best of Client's knowledge, and that Client understands that the Medical provider will be relying upon the truth, accuracy and completeness of such health care information in exercising their own health care judgment in treating Client. Client shall indemnify, defend and hold harmless the Company Parties from and against any liability arising from any inaccuracy or incompleteness of health care information supplied by Client or Client's physician to the Medical Provider.</p>

           <p>1.4 Client shall assume all risks. Client understands and acknowledges that any health care advice, procedure or other service made available by the Choice Matching Services on Client's behalf carries risk. For example, the advice may be incorrect, the procedure may not be successful or may cause injury or have side effects. Client further acknowledges that standards of health care advice, procedures and care abroad may be different than standards in the United States of America or Client's home country. Client accepts and is solely responsible for the risks and will not hold any Company Party responsible in any way.</p>

          <p>1.5 Client shall indemnify Company. Client agrees to defend, indemnify, and hold harmless the Company Parties, from and against any and all claims, proceedings, damages, injuries, liabilities, losses, costs and expenses (including reasonable attorney’s fees and litigation expenses), relating to or arising from services obtained by Client through Company’s Choice Matching Services, for services obtained by Client separately of Company’s Choice Matching Service and for any breach by Client of the terms and conditions of any agreement between Client and Company and between Client and any Provider selected by Client through Company’s Choice Matching Services.</p>


        

          </ol>

