       <h2>COMPANY RESPONSIBILITY</h2>

        <li>
            <br/><br/>
          <ol>

            <p>2.1 Company provides choice matching services Only. Through the relationships that Company has established with various Medical provider including physicians, hospitals, ambulatory surgery centers. Practitioners and imaging centers (the “Medical Provider”), Company matches Medical provider in the United States of America or abroad with health care needs specified by Client (the “Choice Matching Services”). As part of its Choice Matching Services, Company may: (a) make information from and about third parties available to Client; (b) introduce Client to third party Medical provider of services; (c) facilitate communications between Client and such third- party Medical Provider; and/or (d) facilitate the payment of services by Client to such third-party Medical Provider. In assisting in Choice Matching Services between Client and third-party Medical provider of services, Company is acting as an independent contractor to the Client.</p>

            <p>2.2 Company does not offer direct medical health services. Client understands and acknowledges that Company will not provide Client any health care services and that Company itself is not a health care provider, nor an agent of any other party that may provide such services to Client. Third parties independent of Company will provide those services to Client. If Client is not satisfied with any services of any Medical provider for which Company provides Choice Matching Services, including, without limitation, the results of any health care procedures furnished by any Provider, Client's sole remedy is to pursue relief against that Provider and not against Company. Client further understands and acknowledges that in the event of any dispute between Client and any Provider related to the provision of services by such Provider, Client's recourse may be to file a lawsuit either in the United States of America, in Client's home country and/or abroad in order to enforce its rights against such Provider.

        </p>

        <p>2.3 Information on medical provider(s). Company does not recommend any preferred or specific Provider for Client's desired health care treatment. Company’s responsibilities are limited to facilitating contact with, and providing information about, one or more Medical provider within the United States of America or abroad, including their credentials, to assist Client in making informed decisions. Client understands that all information about the Medical Provider, including physician credentials, are supplied by the Medical provider themselves and are not independently verified by Company. Company explicitly disclaims any responsibility for the content, truth, accuracy or completeness of any such information. Even though Company may have provided information regarding the availability of health care services, Client understands that Company takes no responsibility whatsoever and excludes all liability for the actual health care services provided.</p>

        <p>2.4 Warranty Disclaimer. To the fullest extent permissible by law, Company assumes no responsibility nor does it grant any warranties, express or implied, relating to the operation, safety, condition or service of any physician, hospital, or other health care provider and/or products associated with such entities or services that are used wholly or in part by, for or on behalf of Client. Company is not liable for (a) the acts, errors, omissions, representations, warranties, breaches, negligence or professional malpractice of any medical provider or any personal injuries, death, property damage or other damages or expenses resulting from the acts or omissions of the medical provider or any other causes outside of Company’s control, or (b) any liability, claims or damages arising out of or related to Client's health, medical history or condition, or the health care treatment of Client, from any cause whatsoever.</p>

        <p>2.5 Limited Liability. Company shall not be responsible for travel changes, delays or cancellations or for any illness, death, injury, damage or loss of time arising therefrom. Changes to travel itineraries due to mechanical, weather or world events beyond Company’s control, as well as changes in travel itineraries due to Client's health care condition or health care needs, are at the sole discretion of the medical provider of transportation services and may occur without notice. Any applicable compensation resulting from such occurrences is also at the sole discretion of such medical provider. Company shall not be liable for any injuries, damages, or losses caused to Client in connection with, or by the employees or contractors of medical provider, terrorist activities, social or labor unrest, mechanical or construction failures, or difficulties, diseases, local laws, climactic conditions, criminal acts or abnormal conditions or developments, or any other actions, omissions, or conditions outside the control of Company.</p>

        <p>2.6 Limited Damages. Independent of, severable from, and to be enforced independently of any other provision of this Release, COMPANY SHALL NOT BE LIABLE TO CLIENT IN CONTRACT, TORT OR OTHERWISE FOR ANY DAMAGES WHATSOEVER, INCLUDING, WITHOUT LIMITATION, ACTUAL, ECONOMIC, INCIDENTAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, SPECIAL, PUNITIVE, OR EXEMPLARY DAMAGES OF ANY KIND (INCLUDING, WITHOUT LIMITATION, EMOTIONAL DISTRESS OR LOSS OF CONSORTIUM) AS A RESULT OF COMPANY’S PROVISION OF ANY SERVICES TO CLIENT OR ITS AGREEMENT TO PROVIDE SERVICES TO CLIENT, INCLUDING, WITHOUT LIMITATION, ANY FAILURE OF PERFORMANCE OR ANY DEATH OR PERSONAL INJURY RESULTING FROM SERVICES OF THE MEDICAL PROVIDER, IN EXCESS OF THE TOTAL AMOUNT OF FEES (NOT TO INCLUDE ANY EXPENSE REIMBURSEMENTS) ACTUALLY PAID BY CLIENT TO COMPANY HEREUNDER.</p>

     


      </ol>
    </li>


      <h2>GENERAL TERMS</h2>

        <li>
            <br/><br/>
          <ol>

            <p>3.1 Limitation on Actions. Client understands that time is of the essence in investigating and responding to any claim brought by Client against any Company Party. Accordingly, Client agrees that Client shall give written notice of any potential claim arising in any way out of Company’s provision of Choice Matching Services to Client within one (1) year of the date that the claim arose. Client agrees that failure to give such notice is a bar to any action at law or equity against Company arising out of or related to such claim.</p>

            <p>3.2 Governing Laws. This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the State of Illinois.

        </p>

        <p>3.3 Dispute Resolution. Client understands that any dispute that may arises between Client and Company relating to the Choice Matching Services or a breach of this Release must be settled by arbitration in Illinois pursuant to the rules of the American Arbitration Association. Client agrees that within fifteen (30) days after the commencement of arbitration, each Party shall select one person to act as arbitrator, and the two selected shall select a third arbitrator within ten (20) days of their appointment. If the arbitrators selected by the Parties are unable or fail to agree upon the third arbitrator, the third arbitrator shall be selected by the American Arbitration Association.</p>

        <p>3.4 Venue and Jurisdiction. In the event any dispute arises between Client and Company outside of the arbitration provisions, then with respect to any litigation arising from such dispute, Client (a) consents to submit to the personal jurisdiction of any United States federal court located in the State of Illinois or any Illinois state court, (b) agrees not to attempt to deny or defeat such personal jurisdiction by motion or other request for leave from any such court, and (c) agrees not to bring any action relating to such dispute in any court other than a federal court sitting in the State of Illinois or a Illinois state court.</p>

        <p>3.5 Severability. If any provision of this Release, or the application thereof to any person or circumstance, shall be held to any extent to be invalid or unenforceable, the remainder of this Release, or the application of such provision to other persons or circumstances, shall not be affected thereby, and each provision of this Release shall be valid and enforceable to the fullest extent permitted by law.</p>

        <p>3.6 Attorney’s Fees. In the event of any arbitration or legal proceeding arising out of or relating to this Release, then the prevailing Party in such arbitration or litigation shall be entitled to recover its costs of prosecuting and/or defending the same, including, without limitation, reasonable attorney’s fees at trial and all appellate levels</p>
        <p>3.7 Essential Elements; Survival. Client acknowledges and agrees that the limitations contained in this Release are essential to Company, and that Company has expressly relied upon the inclusion of each and every provision herein as a condition to its provision of Choice Matching Services to Client. The Parties further acknowledge and agree that all of the terms and conditions of this Release are intended to, and shall, survive the termination of Choice Matching Services. I have read and understood the foregoing and agree to all of the terms therein.</p>

     


      </ol>
